Subject: Automation Initiative Success: Zero-Touch Infosec Sign-Offs for CCB & ATD Tickets

Dear Leadership Team,

We are pleased to share a significant milestone in our ongoing efforts to drive operational efficiency and process optimization. The KPMG team has successfully developed and deployed a fully automated solution to handle Infosec sign-offs for application security activities.

Historically, processing approvals for CCB (Change Control Board) and ATD tickets required manual intervention to extract, compile, and format vulnerability data across various security domains. To streamline this, our team has engineered a Python-based automation script that entirely eliminates this manual overhead.

How It Works:
The automated system continuously monitors incoming requests. Upon detecting an application code via email, it instantly queries our internal databases and Excel trackers. It dynamically generates comprehensive, interactive HTML reports and reverts to the requester with the necessary attachments—all in real-time.

Key Benefits & Impact:

Zero Human Interaction: The script provides complete end-to-end processing for Infosec sign-offs from the KPMG team, completely removing the need for manual data fetching and email responses.

Accelerated Approvals: By providing instant responses to application code queries, the process for approving CCB and ATD tickets is now significantly smoother and faster, preventing any bottleneck in deployment pipelines.

Comprehensive Security Coverage: The automation intelligently consolidates data across all critical security assessments, automatically generating distinct reports for VAPT, SAST, and SCA (including SLA tracking, Violations, and Security metrics).

Enhanced Accuracy: By removing manual data compilation, we have eliminated the risk of human error, ensuring stakeholders receive highly accurate, up-to-date security postures filtered exactly to their requested application.

This initiative underscores the KPMG team's commitment to delivering value beyond standard security assessments by actively enhancing CRISL’s operational workflows. We look forward to identifying further areas where automation can drive speed and reliability for the organization.

